1. cs.AI - The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning approach that combines a learned transition model with Monte Carlo tree search to solve a block-placing task in Minecraft. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence. 
2. cs.LG - The paper uses deep neural networks to learn the transition model and Monte Carlo tree search to plan the best sequence of actions. This falls under the category of machine learning. 
3. cs.CV - The paper uses visual input in the form of the agent's first-person-view image to solve the block-placing task. This falls under the category of computer vision. 
4. cs.GR - The paper proposes a method to solve a task in Minecraft, which involves interacting with a 3D environment. This falls under the category of graphics. 
5. cs.RO - The paper proposes a method to plan the best sequence of actions for the agent to perform in a dynamic environment. This falls under the category of robotics.
